14
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:11,761
With ten days off,
figured you'd go abroad.

15
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:14,769
But you're off to Yamagata, right?

16
00:02:15,202 --> 00:02:16,072
Yes,

17
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:18,263
Broke up with your boyfriend?

18
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:21,273
I just prefer the countryside.

19
00:02:21,575 --> 00:02:22,655
- See ya!
- Bye!

20
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:24,140
Let's go play!

21
00:02:24,378 --> 00:02:25,748
Bye now!

22
00:02:26,046 --> 00:02:27,566
Later!

23
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,075
Did you get good grades?

24
00:02:30,417 --> 00:02:33,077
No. but I don't care.

25
00:02:33,553 --> 00:02:34,283
How come?

26
00:02:34,488 --> 00:02:37,268
As soon as get home,
we'ra traveling to Grandma's.

27
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:39,778
So l won't get yelled at for ages.

28
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,940
Lucky you!
Are you going away too?

29
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:45,980
Yeah, to Nagano.
How about you, Taeko?

30
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:47,222
I'm not sure.

31
00:02:47,634 --> 00:02:49,773
My Dad bought a summer place.

32
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:51,640
Wow...that's great!

33
00:02:53,774 --> 00:02:56,354
Such a bad grade in math again.

34
00:02:57,411 --> 00:02:59,961
But I got a “B” in science.

35
00:03:00,781 --> 00:03:03,031
Are we going away for the holidays?

36
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:04,709
Not really.

37
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,325
Take me someplace.

38
00:03:08,221 --> 00:03:12,141
I'll take you to a movie.
Find out what's playing.

39
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:15,453
Not that. mean to the country...

40
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:16,719
The country?

41
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:19,010
Like Grandma's country house.

42
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:20,709
Grandma lives with us.

43
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:23,081
- Grandpa's then...
- He's dead.

44
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:27,070
We don't have relatives
in the country, so don't ask.

45
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:35,142
My family had lived in Tokyo
for generations.

46
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:38,406
envied friends who had family
in the countryside.

47
00:03:41,788 --> 00:03:44,478
It's too late to book.
All hotels will be full.

48
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:46,935
But I really want to go...

49
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:49,384
What about “Onoya”?

50
00:03:49,763 --> 00:03:53,363
We're regulars.
They'd have a room for us.

51
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:54,987
Where's that?

52
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:58,275
Good idea.
Taeko's never been there.

53
00:03:58,805 --> 00:03:59,825
That's right.

54
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:02,503
ls it in the mountains...by the sea?

55
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:04,640
It's in Atami.

56
00:04:06,046 --> 00:04:06,946
Atami?

57
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:09,490
You get to ride the bullet train.

58
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,666
Sure, you'll love it.

59
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:16,555
Atami...

60
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:19,220
Lots of different hot springs...

61
00:04:19,793 --> 00:04:22,513
There's a huge Roman Bath.

62
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:28,096
And others, like
the Swan Bath and the Violet Bath.

63
00:04:28,902 --> 00:04:30,482
The beautiful Violet Bath!

64
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:32,888
The Violet Bath...

65
00:04:33,173 --> 00:04:35,163
Oh yes. It's fantastic.

66
00:04:35,542 --> 00:04:37,152
You love hot springs, right?

67
00:04:37,577 --> 00:04:41,327
Since father's working.
you four go.

68
00:04:42,249 --> 00:04:43,209
What?!

69
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,090
Us?

70
00:04:48,355 --> 00:04:49,615
Go too?!

71
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:59,900
I'm amazed you show up every morning.

72
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:02,837
Everyone else has left town.

73
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:07,438
Aren't you going anywhere?

74
00:05:08,074 --> 00:05:09,304
- Yes, I am.
- Where?

75
00:05:09,576 --> 00:05:10,506
Atami.

76
00:05:10,911 --> 00:05:13,661
Atami? What's in Atami?

77
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,727
Hot springs.

78
00:05:19,853 --> 00:05:21,193
It's good timing.

79
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:24,998
We're going away next week.

80
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:28,732
No-one will be around for ages.

81
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:33,572
Hello, Okajima residence.

82
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,359
Nanako? It's Taeko.

83
00:05:36,803 --> 00:05:40,753
l leave today. Any message for
your husband's family?

84
00:05:41,842 --> 00:05:45,762
Not really. Just buy them something.

85
00:05:46,413 --> 00:05:48,903
Say it's from us and
lH pay you back,

86
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:52,369
Don't worry about it. How's Mom?

87
00:05:52,886 --> 00:05:54,226
She's out today.

88
00:05:54,588 --> 00:05:58,368
She was mad you turned down
that guy's proposal.

89
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:02,405
“At 27, that's the best offer
she's going to get!”

90
00:06:02,963 --> 00:06:05,243
It's all she talks about.

91
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:09,065
She's got a point.
You're not young anymore...

92
00:06:09,636 --> 00:06:10,686
Oh, yeah?

93
00:06:10,937 --> 00:06:12,247
Definitely.

94
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:14,649
You've got to settle down eventually.

95
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:18,991
By the way, did you really work
in the fields last year?

96
00:06:19,646 --> 00:06:22,866
Yes, harvesting rice.
This year, I'm picking safflower.

97
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,316
Safflower?

98
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:28,091
Thanks to you, I finally have family
in the countryside.

99
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,741
So, I'm making the most of it!

100
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:35,039
Give me a break!

101
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:38,685
Rather than stay in that old house,

102
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:42,709
why not treat yourself
to a fancy hotel for once?

103
00:06:43,303 --> 00:06:45,143
Maybe you'd meet a nice boy.

104
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:49,589
No way. You mean
a hotel like “Onoya”?

105
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,473
“Onoya”?

106
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,623
Not that again!

107
00:06:56,683 --> 00:06:58,853
You've got to get over it.

108
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,942
Let go of that baggage from the past!

109
00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:16,145
My sisters, of course, would never
go to a place like Atami.

110
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:20,390
Grandma...

111
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:23,354
Almost done?

112
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:26,121
Let's go to another bath.

113
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,556
We just went.

114
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:31,259
Only to the Swan Bath.

115
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:37,590
Bored to tears, went alone
to the Brothers Grimm Bath

116
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:41,175
the Mermaid Bath, the Lemon Bath,

117
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:44,558
and the Violet Bath,
one after the other.

118
00:07:45,065 --> 00:07:46,844
It's enormous!

119
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:50,707
When I got to the Roman Bath,
my head was spinning.

120
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:54,578
It's amazing...

121
00:08:04,851 --> 00:08:06,341
And ! fainted.

122
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:09,790
And with that, my trip was over.

123
00:08:10,223 --> 00:08:13,533
Followed by endless weeks of vacation.

124
00:08:28,108 --> 00:08:33,028
The other day, my sisters and
were remmscing,

125
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:38,121
We couldn't stop laughing

126
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,661
as the memories came flooding back.

127
00:08:46,993 --> 00:08:48,013
Had one before?

128
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:49,751
No, it’s my first time.

129
00:08:50,397 --> 00:08:51,887
I'm the one who asked for it.

130
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,278
Yeah, we know.

131
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,523
Where did you buy it?

132
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,102
Senbikiya in Ginza.

133
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,660
Must have been expensive.

134
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:01,830
How do we eat it?

135
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:03,222
Slice it into rings.

136
00:09:03,476 --> 00:09:04,766
But how?

137
00:09:06,946 --> 00:09:08,206
I don't know.

138
00:09:09,616 --> 00:09:12,396
Didn't you ask in the store?

139
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:19,536
We'll eat it next Sunday.

140
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,003
Why not now?!

141
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:24,712
We don’t know how.

142
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,407
I'll have a banana.

143
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:31,165
Me too.

144
00:09:34,841 --> 00:09:38,651
Strange fruit they have
in those hot countries.

145
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,308
I'm home!

146
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:45,580
I know how to eat the pineapple!

147
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,059
Really?

148
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:53,221
I'll take that.

149
00:09:54,127 --> 00:09:55,266
Mind your fingers.

150
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:57,548
Wouldn't a carving knife be best?

151
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:12,760
What a nice smell.

152
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,068
It smells so good.

153
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:28,023
I see.

154
00:10:29,262 --> 00:10:30,571
Get plates. Quick.

155
00:10:30,864 --> 00:10:32,854
Okay.

156
00:10:34,934 --> 00:10:36,044
Let us eat.

157
00:10:57,924 --> 00:10:59,473
It's hard.

158
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:05,516
It's not very good.

159
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:07,202
Not so sweet.

160
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,310
Nothing like the canned stuff.

161
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:13,039
Live long enough and you see
lots of different things.

162
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:20,861
- You can have mine.
- Mine too.

163
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,359
It's delicious...

164
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,071
Don't force yourself.

165
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:01,853
You'll get a stomachache.

166
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:13,857
What a let down.

167
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:18,863
Bananas taste much better.

168
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:20,319
You're so right.

169
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:23,323
Bananas are still the king of fruits.

170
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:24,920
I'll have one now.

171
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:54,809
The king of fruit is...

172
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:57,652
the banana, after all.

173
00:13:03,116 --> 00:13:07,276
The year I fainted at the baths and
had my first pineapple...

174
00:13:08,321 --> 00:13:12,131
the Beatles came to Japan,
Started the rock'n'roll band

175
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:15,279
and electric guitar craze.

176
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:23,358
My sister Nanako, a freshman in
art school, was up on all the trends.

177
00:13:24,704 --> 00:13:26,814
Yeah, the Beatles’ lyrics are great.

178
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:33,976
When she wore a mini-skirt, she'd
cover her bottom going up the stairs.

179
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:42,640
My clever sister, Yaeko, was crazy
about some Takarazuka actress.

180
00:13:43,423 --> 00:13:44,593
Yaeko...

181
00:13:46,092 --> 00:13:47,582
I told you to knock!

182
00:13:52,098 --> 00:13:56,818
My sisters' memories are
mainly of fashion and pop trends.

183
00:13:57,870 --> 00:14:02,230
For them, 1966 is the
height of nostalgia.

184
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:06,336
Whereas ! was only ten years old.

185
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:11,089
My favorite band had yet to debut...

186
00:14:11,651 --> 00:14:15,721
My only memories are the back and
forth between school and home.

187
00:14:16,389 --> 00:14:18,119
...fiine was pinned on the wall!

188
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:20,358
That's nice.

189
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:24,623
And it might be entered in
an essay contest.

190
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:27,478
So, teacher kept it.

191
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:31,257
- I'd be so happy...
- You didn't finish lunch again.

192
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:34,558
Why do you hide the pickles
inside the bread?

193
00:14:34,941 --> 00:14:36,611
‘Cause I hate them.

194
00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:40,103
I've got to throw it away.
What a waste.

195
00:14:41,247 --> 00:14:42,887
Such a picky eater!

196
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:49,370
I'd rather you were a good eater
than a good essay writer.

197
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:09,432
How can you drink that stuff?

198
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:14,840
Milk's okay. It's onions I hate.

199
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:18,635
I'm leaving carrots
so I've got no choice.

200
00:15:19,952 --> 00:15:23,962
Who decided we can only
leave one thing?

201
00:15:24,624 --> 00:15:25,614
Shall 1 drink it?

202
00:15:25,858 --> 00:15:26,938
Would you?

203
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:30,057
You'll eat my onions next time?

204
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,895
- Carrots?
- We're allowed one thing!

205
00:15:54,554 --> 00:15:56,194
Two bowls is gross.

206
00:15:57,356 --> 00:15:59,546
People who run in the corridor...

207
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:04,439
...when the hall monitor says
stop, should be punished.

208
00:16:05,531 --> 00:16:08,221
How are you gonna do that?

209
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:10,341
They shouldn't do it.

210
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:11,733
That's right.

211
00:16:12,038 --> 00:16:13,708
You might bump into someone.

212
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,849
If ! bumped into you
I'd bounce a mile!

213
00:16:18,478 --> 00:16:19,468
Get lost!

214
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:23,851
Running is no big deal.

215
00:16:24,283 --> 00:16:25,243
l agree!

216
00:16:25,585 --> 00:16:28,575
- Let's change the rule.
- But we already decided.

217
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:31,472
Raise your hand if you want to speak.

218
00:16:32,258 --> 00:16:34,038
- Here!
- Miss Tani.

219
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:39,365
The hall monitor
should chase the offender,

220
00:16:39,932 --> 00:16:42,152
catch them and punish them.

221
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:45,166
Mr. Suzuki.

222
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:49,786
Then the hall monitor should
be punished for running too.

223
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:51,603
He's right! He's right!

224
00:16:52,245 --> 00:16:53,555
Way to go!

225
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:54,796
He's right.

226
00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:56,824
Miss Tani.

227
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:01,820
The hall monitor shouldn't
be punished because...

228
00:17:03,356 --> 00:17:07,455
.. it's like a policeman
chasing a speeding car.

229
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,233
Any objections?

230
00:17:18,503 --> 00:17:19,934
It makes sense...

231
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:21,759
No more running.

232
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:27,228
So, the hall monitor
can chase offenders.

233
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:31,306
Any other issues?

234
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:33,948
Miss Tani.

235
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,127
- Her again.
- Busybody.

236
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:37,592
Be quiet.

237
00:17:37,857 --> 00:17:39,966
Some people don't finish lunch.

238
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:44,892
I just read an article
on the Vietnam War.

239
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:48,988
There are many
unfortunate people overseas.

240
00:17:49,535 --> 00:17:50,905
We're very lucky.

241
00:17:51,203 --> 00:17:52,873
Lucky to have you near me!

242
00:17:56,309 --> 00:17:59,329
We should be grateful for our food.

243
00:17:59,845 --> 00:18:04,095
We're allowed to leave
one thing on our plates,

244
00:18:05,151 --> 00:18:06,411
but I think it's wrong!

245
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:11,618
Goody two-shoes.

246
00:18:12,391 --> 00:18:16,311
- It can't hurt to leave one thing.
- Let's all leave milk...

247
00:18:16,963 --> 00:18:19,743
- Give it to someone else...
- Of course.

248
00:18:20,232 --> 00:18:23,831
- People hide leftovers in bread.
- That's cheating!

249
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:26,237
I hate school food.

250
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:28,979
If you want to speak,
raise your hand!

251
00:18:30,042 --> 00:18:32,232
What a revolting situation.

252
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:38,911
That night in bed,
after chatting to my sisters

253
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:43,740
more memories from fifth grade

254
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:47,296
came rushing back.

255
00:18:50,763 --> 00:18:54,862
Our pet dog...school sports day...

256
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:58,548
being scared by gross
horror comics...

257
00:19:00,239 --> 00:19:02,579
longing for an electric
pencil-sharpener...

258
00:19:04,677 --> 00:19:08,246
So many little details,
one after the other...

259
00:19:09,215 --> 00:19:12,725
playing in my head like a movie,

260
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:15,949
almost overpowering me.

261
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,899
Is there a Miss Okajima here?

262
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:25,633
That's her.

263
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:40,649
Hirota in our class
says he likes you.

264
00:19:45,918 --> 00:19:46,908
Let's go.

265
00:19:50,056 --> 00:19:52,576
We'll say we told you.

266
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,167
Told you.

267
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:03,671
Where is it?

268
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:04,836
Over there.

